  "summary": "clickpy beacons host identifiers to oast.fun on require",
  "details": "On require('clickpy'), index.js collects host identifiers (hostname, username, platform, arch, cwd, pid, timestamp) and sends them as query parameters via HTTPS GET to a hardcoded out-of-band testing subdomain `qaxiussmufvtouqkuqkenm99nqrzkth05.oast.fun` (Burp Collaborator). The package has no other functionality — package.json has empty description, empty author, no repository — and the sole effect of installing/importing it is to leak identifying information about the installer's machine to an attacker-controlled endpoint. This is the canonical shape of a dependency-confusion or reconnaissance probe.",
